Command-line arguments for splunk-tui.

Configuration precedence (highest to lowest): X. CLI arguments (e.g., --profile, --config-path) X. Environment variables (e.g., SPLUNK_PROFILE, SPLUNK_BASE_URL) X. Profile configuration (from config.json) X. Default values

Usage: splunk-tui [OPTIONS]

Options:
  -p, --profile <PROFILE>
          Config profile name to load

      --config-path <CONFIG_PATH>
          Path to a custom configuration file

      --log-dir <LOG_DIR>
          Directory for log files
          
          [default: logs]

      --no-mouse
          Disable mouse support

      --skip-tutorial
          Skip the first-run tutorial

      --fresh
          Start with fresh state, ignoring any persisted state

      --metrics-bind <METRICS_BIND>
          Enable Prometheus metrics endpoint and bind address (e.g., "localhost:X")
          
          When enabled, exposes /metrics endpoint for Prometheus scraping.
          
          [env: SPLUNK_METRICS_BIND=]

      --otlp-endpoint <OTLP_ENDPOINT>
          Enable OpenTelemetry tracing and specify OTLP endpoint (e.g., "http://localhost:X")
          
          When enabled, traces are exported to the specified OTLP endpoint. Can also be set via SPLUNK_OTLP_ENDPOINT environment variable.
          
          [env: SPLUNK_OTLP_ENDPOINT=]

      --otel-service-name <OTEL_SERVICE_NAME>
          Service name for OpenTelemetry traces
          
          [env: SPLUNK_OTEL_SERVICE_NAME=]

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

  -V, --version
          Print version

Examples:
  splunk-tui
  splunk-tui --profile production
  splunk-tui --config-path /etc/splunk-tui/config.json
  splunk-tui --log-dir /var/log/splunk-tui --no-mouse
  splunk-tui --skip-tutorial
  splunk-tui --fresh
